<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-772-704  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 772 704.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>InfoWorld  August 20 1990 v12 n34 p75(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Keynote secretary manual provides easy data access; menu-drivenguide is full of valuable features. (Digital Learning Systems'Keynotes' Complete Secretary's Handbook) (Software Review)(Impressions) (evaluation)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Darling, Harriet.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Digital Learning Systems' $89.95 Keynotes' Complete Secretary'sHandbook is an electronic book that can be loaded as aterminate-and-stay resident (TSR) or a separate program.andP;  It canoperate as a standard full-screen application under MicrosoftWindows.andP;  The Handbook is laid out like a secretarial textbook,with three main sections and seven appendices listed in the tableof contents.andP;  The Bookmark menu functions like Post-It notes andthe F1 key provides information about the commands.andP;  No mouse isused with the program which is unfortunate.andP;  Mouse support wouldhave enhanced ease of use.andP;  The Handbook runs under MS-DOS 2.1 orlater, or under Windows or Desqview.andP;  It needs a hard drive and atleast 53Kbytes of available memory.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Digital Learning Systems Inc. (products).andO;Product:   Keynotes' Complete Secretary's Handbook (Educational software).andO;Topic:     EvaluationEducational SoftwareUser Aids.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>